AB  - The recycling of REEs from the end of life (EoL) products, such as
nickel metal hydride batteries (NiMH), offers great opportunities for
their supply in Europe. In the presented paper, the application of
‘green’ extractants such as citric (CA), metatartaric (TA), and
ethylenediaminedisuccinic acid (EDDS) (also with H2O2 addition) for
the recovery of REEs was studied. The studies were conducted
considering the effects of the phase contact time, the initial
concentration of CA, TA, and EDDS, as well as H2O2, pH, and
temperature. It was found that the addition of TA to the CA solution
meant that higher rates of metal ion binding and, thus, leaching was
observed. The optimal conditions were obtained in the system: CA-TA
and H2O2 for the concentration 0.6M-0.3 M-2%.
