AB  - PCBs, as one of the most valuable streams of e-waste, are a
considerable source of precious metals, but also contain considerable
amounts of plastic and ceramic. These non-metallic fractions interfere
with and can inhibit the efficiency of metal recovery, particularly
for precious and rare earth metals, which are present in e-waste in
very low concentrations. In this work, electro-mechanical
pre-treatment was applied in order to remove ceramic and plastic
fractions from e-waste prior to the application of the bioleaching
process. Metal content with and without mechanical separation, as well
as metal dissolution and behaviour in the bioleaching process were
compared. The results obtained illustrate the beneficial effects of
separating the metallic from the non-metallic fraction prior the
bioleaching process for the recovery of precious, rare earth and base
metals from e-waste.
